Doulingo makes it very clear and easy to follow. NO STRESS or unclear pathways. Bottom Line: I would recommend this learning tool as it is free and definitely useful. And for anyone who is asking " What's the catch?" they don't send tons of spam emails, or force you to pay for things that are ABSOLUTELY NECESSARY. They do however, often pop ads for their "Duolingo Plus" meaning extra benefits. It says 5 min a day, but in reality of you want to learn a language in under 5 yrs you should spend 20

In terms of a learning experience, thisbis absolutely excellent. I wish there a were a few extra key features, particularly with languages with a non-Latin alphabet (I'm learning Russian), in particular a reference guide to the basic phonics of the letters. also, I wish there was a way to view and review the vocabulary learned up to a certain point. That said, whilst they're "nice to have" improvements, so far very impressed!

This app has some serious problems in translation: namely grammar and word choice. English may not have an official plural of "you," but "y'all" and "you all" are acceptable substitutes- the singular "you" only leads to confusion. It also chooses a lot of less used words instead of the most common form. That is not optimal for new language learners. Finally, this app has a terrible habit of quizzing on vocabulary it has not taught you yet, without the helpful pictures. Use as a supplement only.

I used to love it, but then they got rid of groups (no encouragement, no sharing learning resources, less help) & added leaderboards for all languages combined. Some languages require more focus on sounds & meaning as they don't use Roman script. They can't compete with European languages. Learning too fast or too much doesn't let you absorb the lessons. for some languages you'll find yourself sacrificing sounds for meanings or even meaning itself & passing by "remembering" the sentence.

It's fun, it's free, and I think it's made a positive difference in my life. The concept of the leader boards and maintaining a study streak really has motivated me. My only dislike is that they recently added the requirement of spending 5 lingots (in game currency) to test out of lessons. The alternative is buying the Plus membership. But I won't fault them majorly for that. Overall I would recommend it for beginning to learn a language, I can't speak for obtaining fluency yet .

I used to love it, but then they got rid of groups (no encouragement, no sharing learning resources, less help) & added leaderboards for all languages combined. Some languages require more focus on sounds & meaning as they don't use Roman script. They can't compete with European languages. Learning too fast or too much doesn't let you absorb the lessons. for some languages you'll find yourself sacrificing sounds for meanings or even meaning itself & passing by "remembering" the sentence.

It's fun, it's free, and I think it's made a positive difference in my life. The concept of the leader boards and maintaining a study streak really has motivated me. My only dislike is that they recently added the requirement of spending 5 lingots (in game currency) to test out of lessons. The alternative is buying the Plus membership. But I won't fault them majorly for that. Overall I would recommend it for beginning to learn a language, I can't speak for obtaining fluency yet .

So far im enjoying the app. I think this app is good for an "Introduction" to a language you have interest in - and should you like it, you should then continue the study by taking in a language class in addition. Duolingo is good for introducing and practicing a new language, but its not a substitute for a proper class.

After being very happy with the free service, I chose the paid subscription for offline use and was very disappointed. Charges (for 1 year) were some R1241. 86 all inclusive, debited upfront. That's just a rip off for an online language course. The meager benefits of Plus (paid subscription) compared with free subscription just don't justify the expense. I might consider a month to month paid subscription but it's only really useful on aeroplane flights where I don't have internet.
